# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Security: never commit secrets or stored participant data.
# These patterns apply repo-wide as defense-in-depth (subprojects may also have
# their own .gitignore). gitignore does NOT untrack already-committed files —
# see SECURITY.md if something sensitive was committed in the past.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Environment / secret files (admin seed password, DB path, API keys, etc.).
# Keep the *.env.example templates, which must contain no real secrets.
.env
.env.*
*.env
!.env.example
!*.env.example

# SQLite study databases — contain participant PII (emails, demographics) and
# their rankings. Must never be disclosed in the repository.
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
data/

# AWS / cloud credential files that occasionally land in a project dir.
.aws/
*.pem
credentials.json

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build artifacts, dependencies, OS/editor cruft
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
dist/
dist-ssr/
*.log

.DS_Store
*.swp

# Large generated image set (not study data, just bulky)
processed_images
